<HL>
   World Bank Clears
   Two Loans to India
</HL>
<DATE>
06/29/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A14
</SO>
<CO>
   AFRIC FREST
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
BANKS (BNK)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The World Bank approved two loans totaling
$583 million to India to help finance electric power
facilities.
   The bank also cleared $275 million in loans to Nigeria to
upgrade the country's telecommunications network and help
finance urban development projects.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The International Development Association, a bank
affiliate, approved a $50 million credit to Mauritania to
restructure some public enterprises and close down others.
</TEXT>
